          "description": "Had a great experience here. Everyone was friendly and it was super efficient; I didn't wait at all. Stacy was my medical assistant and ran me through the preliminary work. With a smile on her face she told me all my numbers look bad, but that's my fault so it's OK. She was nice about it. Tamia was my take home equipment specialist genius and took the time to make sure I understood how to use everything. She even quizzed me 3 times on everything. I did poorly, but again that's my fault. Next time I will study. Dr. Govi had excellent bedside manner, was receptive to all my questions, and explained things in the right amount of detail. He also did not do anything to increase my blood pressure higher than it already is. End to end one of the best experiences I've had at a medical office. Like walking into a bar where everybody knows you but instead of taking your cash they take your blood. Highly recommend.",
